article.headline: Vermont 78, Binghamton 69
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Marqus Blakely scored 17 points, blocked three shots and had two steals in Vermont's 78-69 win over Binghamton in the regular season finale for both teams on Sunday. The Catamounts (22-9, 12-4 America East Conference) scored 15 points off 11 turnovers, including six off three Bearcats' giveaways in a key late run. Binghamton (13-8, 8-8) pulled within 67-63 with 3:24 remaining, but ran into turnover trouble. Following a Bearcats' turnover, Maurice Joseph grabbed the offensive rebound on a blocked shot and hit a layup with 2:48 left for a 67-63 Vermont lead. Blakely then stole the inbounds pass and Garvey Young's uncontested layup gave the Bearcats a 72-63 lead with 2:40 remaining. Blakely turned a Dylan Talley turnover into an 11-point advantage with 2 minutes left. Talley finished with 20 points for Binghamton, which snapped a two-game winning streak.
